<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="33" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
Previously known only from the type locality in Papua New Guinea, this tall tree species in section 
<taxonomicName class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Aglaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Podocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="section" section="Amoora">Amoora</taxonomicName>
, has the largest fruits recorded for the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Aglaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aglaia" order="Podocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Aglaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Collections from West Papua are of immature fruits and flower buds.
</paragraph>
